  <section id="about" class="card">
    <h2>Why This Matters</h2>
    <p>Injuries don't just affect the body—they can deeply impact the mind. Student-athletes often struggle with identity loss, isolation, and anxiety during recovery. This project is designed to help you stay strong—physically and mentally.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="resources" class="card">
    <h2>Resources for Recovery</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Mental Resilience Tips:</strong> Journaling, mindfulness, visualization, positive self-talk.</li>
      <li><strong>Helplines:</strong> National Alliance on Mental Illness (NAMI) - 1-800-950-NAMI</li>
      <li><strong>Podcasts:</strong> Coming soon – interviews with athletes who bounced back stronger.</li>
      <li><strong>Books:</strong> "The Champion’s Comeback" by Jim Afremow</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

